---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import FAQItem from '../components/FAQItem.astro';
import ReportPreview from '../components/ReportPreview.astro';

const description = 'How the weekly competitive intelligence report works. What we track, how we write it, and answers to the questions business owners ask before they sign up.';

const productLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Product',
  name: 'Weekly Competitive Intelligence Report',
  description,
  brand: { '@type': 'Brand', name: 'AI Lean Solutions' },
  category: 'Business Intelligence Subscription',
};
---

<Base title="Product" description={description} jsonLd={productLd}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pt-20 pb-16 md:pt-28 bg-grain">
    <div class="aurora"></div>
    <div class="container-site relative">
      <p class="section-label mb-6">// Product</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold tracking-tightest text-[clamp(2rem,6vw,4.5rem)] leading-[1.02] max-w-[18ch]">
        One email per week.<br/>
        <span class="text-gradient">Four steps before it hits your inbox.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Here&rsquo;s exactly what happens between us and your tracked competitors during the
        week, and what ends up in front of you when the next report arrives.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Steps -->
  <Section num="01" eyebrow="How it works">
    <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-16">

      <article class="relative">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-label text-brand-cyan mb-3">Step 1 · Onboarding</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
          We find your real competitors.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Not the national franchise five miles away. Not the place that serves a different
          income band. The local businesses actually pulling from your customer pool. We start
          with geography, match on service mix and price point, and send you the list before
          we start tracking. You get final say &mdash; swap any of them if our match is off.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="relative">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-label text-brand-cyan mb-3">Step 2 · Daily watching</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
          We watch them every day.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Their websites, Google Business Profiles, Instagram, Yelp, Facebook, licensing
          boards, and any public pricing pages. Daily snapshots, compared against the prior
          week&rsquo;s snapshot. We don&rsquo;t log into anything we shouldn&rsquo;t. We don&rsquo;t pull
          anything that isn&rsquo;t public. This is the boring, patient part. It&rsquo;s the part
          nobody else actually does.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="relative">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-label text-brand-cyan mb-3">Step 3 · End-of-week review</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
          We catch what actually changed.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Most &ldquo;changes&rdquo; are noise. A new Instagram reel isn&rsquo;t a move. A price
          card update is. A new staff member on the team page is. A run of one-star reviews
          is. We sort signal from noise, rank by real-world impact, and write a draft. Brian
          reviews and edits it before it goes out.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="relative">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-label text-brand-cyan mb-3">Step 4 · Report arrives</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
          You read it with your coffee.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Your weekly competitive intelligence arrives as a plain email. About a six-minute
          read. Three sections: what changed, where you stand, and three specific moves to
          consider this week. Written in plain language by someone who&rsquo;s actually run a
          business.
        </p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Sample report -->
  <Section num="02" eyebrow="Sample">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.3fr] md:items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold tracking-tightest text-4xl leading-[1.05]">
          See a full report.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-text-muted text-[17px] leading-relaxed max-w-prose">
          Radiance Aesthetics is a fictional Phoenix med spa, but the format, voice, and
          data types are exactly what a real subscriber gets each week.
        </p>
        <a href="/sample-report/radiance-aesthetics.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary mt-8">
          Read the full sample
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M2 6h8m-3-3 3 3-3 3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div><ReportPreview /></div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <Section num="03" eyebrow="Questions we get">
    <h2 class="font-display font-bold tracking-tightest text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-[1.05] max-w-[18ch]">
      Things business owners ask before signing up.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-12 max-w-3xl">
      <FAQItem question="How do you pick my competitors?">
        <p>Geography first &mdash; typically a 3- to 10-mile radius depending on how people
          actually travel for your service. Then we match on service mix and price band. We send
          you the list before tracking starts, and you can swap any of them. Onboarding takes
          about four days.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="Can I override the competitors you pick?">
        <p>Yes. Every one of them. We default to matching on service and geography, but you know
          your market. If you think the place six blocks away is actually your main competitor
          because of how referrals flow, tell us and we&rsquo;ll track them instead.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="How is this different from Google Alerts or Birdeye?">
        <p>Google Alerts tells you when a competitor&rsquo;s name shows up on the internet &mdash;
          mostly press releases and spam. Birdeye shows you review aggregation, which is one of
          the things we watch. Neither one tells you &ldquo;they raised their prices on Thursday
          and rolled out a discount on Friday &mdash; here&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;d do about it.&rdquo;
          That&rsquo;s the gap we fill.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="Do I need to install anything?">
        <p>No. The entire product is an email. No dashboards, no logins, no browser extensions,
          no mobile app. If you can read an email, you have the full product.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="Is my data shared with other subscribers?">
        <p>No. Each subscriber&rsquo;s report is built from public information about their
          competitors &mdash; we don&rsquo;t ask you for customer lists, pricing, or internal
          numbers, and we don&rsquo;t share anything across accounts. Your name only appears in
          our own subscriber records.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="What if my competitors subscribe too?">
        <p>They&rsquo;d see reports about their competitors, and you&rsquo;d see reports about
          yours. The two reports would contain different information. If two subscribers happen
          to track each other, the system handles that without exposing either one&rsquo;s
          subscription.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="How much human review goes into each report?">
        <p>Every report. Brian personally reviews the draft of every weekly email before it goes
          out during the first 12 months of each industry launch. Software handles the watching
          and drafting. A real person signs off on the recommendations.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="What if I cancel?">
        <p>You cancel. We stop sending. We hold your email address for 30 days in case you want
          to come back, then delete everything except what we need for tax records. There is no
          contract, no cancellation fee, and no &ldquo;retention specialist&rdquo; who will call
          you.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="Will there be a phone call or demo I need to sit through?">
        <p>Not unless you want one. The whole process is: you read the site, you read a sample
          report, you decide, you sign up. Brian will reply to any email you send him, but we
          don&rsquo;t schedule demos, discovery calls, or &ldquo;quick intro chats.&rdquo;</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="What industries does this work for?">
        <p>Any local service business where a handful of local competitors matter more than
          national chains. Med spas, dental, veterinary, boutique fitness, HVAC, home services,
          specialty retail, private-practice healthcare. We&rsquo;re launching one industry at
          a time so the reports are sharp. Tell us where to go next.</p>
      </FAQItem>

      <FAQItem question="How much does it cost?">
        <p>Pricing is sent in response to your waitlist signup or a direct email to Brian.
          We&rsquo;re intentionally not listing it on the site &mdash; founding-member pricing
          is different from standard pricing, and we&rsquo;d rather walk through which applies
          to you before sending numbers.</p>
      </FAQItem>
    </div>
  </Section>

</Base>
